Here’s how GPS tracking works and how it can help you recover your vehicle if it’s ever stolen. Real-time GPS car tracking is a system used to pinpoint the position of your car. There are both simple and expanded forms of vehicle tracking with a variety of functions depending on your individual needs. There are several reasons each type of system is useful to you. There is a basic functioning system called passive car tracking. This will help you locate the whereabouts of a vehicle within 24 hours on any day of the year. It will trace the car’s journey, storing those points in a computer. Alternatively, an active system has more advanced functions to trace even more information. It can provide information such as the speed the car is travelling in real time, and relay this information directly to a computer or mobile telephone. This stores information in real time and is often much more helpful than a passive tracking system. The benefits of possessing this type of real-time GPS car tracking are numerous. First, you will be able to gain immediate assistance in the event of trouble. Simply press a button in the event of a robbery or other emergency and the authorities will arrive straightaway. It also makes searching for your vehicle efficient if it is stolen, and will significantly increase recovery time. It can help the police find your car to be returned to you. However, a GPS tracker won’t stop your car from being stolen in the first place. That’s why it’s important to have a good anti-theft system in place as well. This way, you can deter thieves and make it more likely that your car will be returned to you. Car tracking systems can also be helpful if you lock yourself out of your vehicle. You can simply call your service and wait a short time for your car to be unlocked. Another use is to be able to locate your car in a large parking lot. You will never have to walk up and down rows trying to find your car again. Simply use your service to have your car signalled to you. If you’re thinking of getting a GPS tracker for your car, be sure to do your research and find one that’s right for you. There are many different types of GPS trackers on the market, and not all of them are created equal. Make sure you choose one that offers the features you need and that will work well in your particular situation. GPS tracking can be a great way to keep your car safe, but it’s not a foolproof solution. Be sure to take other precautions as well to ensure the safety of your vehicle.